title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\InterconnectOutageNotification
name: InterconnectOutageNotification
description:
Description of a planned outage on this Interconnect.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.InterconnectOutageNotification

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.affected_circuits
params.description: If issue_type is IT_PARTIAL_OUTAGE, a list of the Google-side circuit IDs that will be affected.

params.name: data.description
params.description: A description about the purpose of the outage.

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Scheduled end time for the outage (milliseconds since Unix epoch).

params.name: data.issue_type
params.description: Form this outage is expected to take, which can take one of the following values: - OUTAGE: The Interconnect may be completely out of service for some or all of the specified window. - PARTIALOUTAGE: Some circuits comprising the Interconnect as a whole should remain up, but with reduced bandwidth. Note that the versions of this enum prefixed with "IT" have been deprecated in favor of the unprefixed values. Check the IssueType enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.source
params.description: The party that generated this notification, which can take the following value: - GOOGLE: this notification as generated by Google. Note that the value of NSRC_GOOGLE has been deprecated in favor of GOOGLE. Check the Source enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: Scheduled start time for the outage (milliseconds since Unix epoch).

params.name: data.state
params.description: State of this notification, which can take one of the following values: - ACTIVE: This outage notification is active. The event could be in the past, present, or future. See start_time and endtime for scheduling. - CANCELLED: The outage associated with this notification was cancelled before the outage was due to start. - COMPLETED: The outage associated with this notification is complete. Note that the versions of this enum prefixed with "NS" have been deprecated in favor of the unprefixed values. Check the State enum for the list of possible values.
